definitions.definition: The act of occupying , the state of being occupied or the state of being an occupant or tenant .
The period of time during which someone rents or otherwise occupies certain land or premises .
examples: They had a five-year occupancy on the house.

definitions.definition: The specific use to which something occupied is put.
examples: This building is for residential occupancy .
